description_of_deviation: As part of the protocol for the processing of maternal blood samples collected during the INDiGO trial, dried blood spots (DBS) are supposed to be collected and stored for the subsequent analysis of iodine metabolites, as a secondary measure of maternal iodine status. However, due to an error on the part of the laboratory staff working on the trial, all blood samples collected between 5th May 2023 to 31st August 2023 had this step missed. Therefore, these secondary outcome measures will not be available although the main measure of maternal iodine status (urinary iodine concentration) will still be available. This is in contravention of section 7.3 of INDiGO SSP011_ Maternal and Infant Dried Blood Spot Collection and Storage V1.0. Samples (i.e. from 20 and 28-week clinic visits)from this participant are part of the total of samples from 55 participants that were affected with a total of 89 (Visit 20 =55, Visit 28 =27 and Visit 36=3) DBS missed.
reason_for_deviation: Omission of a sample processing step by the laboratory team.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi:
The attention of the lab team was immediately drawn to this deviation and the specific lab manual reviewed with the entire lab team.
Further, to prevent this from reoccurring, the following actions have been recommended by the INDiGO project team to the Keneba laboratory manager:
1. The fields for preparation of DBS will be made mandatory fields on REDCap to ensure that reasons are provided if DBS are not prepared.
2. A refresher on the study procedures including lab processes is scheduled for the entire team.

description_of_deviation:
All the stored plasma, and urine samples that were collected during the Visit 20 clinic visit belonging to this participant were removed from their position in the freezer by a staff member not working on INDiGO and not replaced. As a result, they were left overnight at room temperature and allowed to thaw for a period of 19 hours and 35 mins (i.e. from 17:00 hrs on 28th May- 12:35 PM on 29th May 2023) afternoon on the 29th of May 2023). This is in contravention to Section 11.4 of version 4.0 of the INDiGO trial study protocol which requires aliquots of blood, breast milk and urine from participating women and blood and stool samples from infants to be kept frozen at - 70oC for future analysis.  In total: 2 aliquots of LH, 2 aliquots of EDTA and 4 aliquots of urine were affected.

The study PI is in discussion with the trial collaborators with regard to the likely impact this freeze-thaw-refreeze cycle will have on the samples and biomarker integrity. So far, the discussions have been reassuring from the point of view that the majority of the micronutrient biomarkers are likely to have been degraded in the samples. 

We also note that this non-compliance report is being submitted beyond the recommended five-day window. This is because the full report from the laboratory with sample details was delayed in reaching the PI.
reason_for_deviation: Poor laboratory practice by a member of another project team.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi:
The samples were immediately returned to the -80 freezer after notifying the lab manager about the incident. 

Further, to prevent this from reoccurring, the following actions have been recommended by the INDiGO project team to the Keneba laboratory manager:

1. A study-specific freezer is allocated, so non-INDiGO staff are unable to access INDiGO samples.

2. Study freezers are only used for samples and not for the storage of dry ice, ice packs etc.

description_of_deviation: This participant's blood samples collected during her Week 20 Clinic visit were delivered to the lab beyond 30 mins from the time of collection as specified in the INDiGO trial SSP06_VenousBloodSampleCollection_v01. However, they were delivered to the lab within 4 hours of collection as specified in the MRCG' unit SOP and no issues related to the samples' integrity was raised by the lab.
reason_for_deviation: This was an oversight from the team. Also, the time span for the delivery of samples to the lab following the collection of samples is very short.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi: The attention of the team was called to this deviation. The SSP related to this process is revised and updated to align the time allowance for the delivery of blood samples to the lab with its corresponding unit SOP. will amend the SSP to be more in line with the Unit SOP while ensuring the integrity of the samples. We propose a timeline of two hours from collection to delivery as the upper limit but will target 30 minutes as optimal.

description_of_deviation: This participant missed IP supplementation for more than 5 consecutive days (from 3rd June-19th June) in contravention of section 5.1.3 of version 5.0 of the INDiGO study protocol. Her weekly morbidity form was also not completed during this time.
reason_for_deviation: This participant travelled outside the study area to provide care for her sick mother. Although she notified the team before travelling, she could not be followed up at the coast for supplementation or form completion. However constant communication was maintained with her while she was away from the study area to address any safety concerns in the event she has any, and to know her return date for continuation of IP supplementation.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi: The investigation team is working on establishing a subunit of field staff that will be responsible for following up of participants who travelled outside the study area where and when possible. In addition, where a participant is absent from the study area and face to face follow up is not possible, her weekly morbidity forms will still be completed but using a phone interview, rather than face to face.
resonsible_person: Dr Ousman Jarjou  and Dr Sophie Moore

description_of_deviation:
Participant pair IN-C-009C and IN-M-009K missed all assessments at the 6 month clinic 
visit and the 6month HOME assessment. 
This is categorised as a major noncompliance due to impact on the quality of data. 
Assessments Affected 
IN-M-009K: 6mo Clinical Review, 6mo anthropometrics and vital signs, 6mo urine 
sample collection and processing, 6mo blood sample collection and processing, 6mo 
breast milk sample collection and processing.
reason_for_deviation:
The participant pair are residing away from West Kiang for an extended period of time. 
The 6 month assessments were overdue by 2 months and therefore categorized as 
missed.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi: The participant pair will be withdrawn from the study

description_of_deviation: This participant's blood samples collected during her Week 20 Clinic visit were delivered to the lab beyond 30 mins from the time of collection as specified in the INDiGO trial SSP06_VenousBloodSampleCollection_v01_Final. However, they were delivered to the lab within 4 hours of collection as specified in the MRCG' unit SOP and no issues related to the samples' integrity was raised by the lab.
reason_for_deviation: This was an oversight from the team and the stipulated time for delivery of blood samples to the lab seems very short.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi: The attention of the team was called to this deviation. The SSP related to this process was revised and updated to align the time allowance for the delivery of blood samples to the lab with its corresponding unit SOP.SSP is revised an updated, and a refresher was conducted on 02-06-2023.

description_of_deviation:
All the stored plasma, and urine samples that were collected during the Visit 20 clinic visit belonging to this participant were removed from their position in the freezer by a staff member not working on INDiGO and not replaced. As a result, they were left overnight at room temperature and allowed to thaw for a period of 19 hours and 35 mins (i.e from 17:00 hrs on 28th May- 12:35 PM on 29th May 2023) afternoon on the 29th of May 2023). This is in contravention to Section 11.4 of version 4.0 of the INDiGO trial study protocol which requires aliquots of blood, breast milk and urine from participating women and blood and stool samples from infants to be kept frozen at - 70oC for future analysis.  In total: 2 aliquots of LH,  2 aliquots of EDTA  and 4 aliquots of urine were affected.

The study PI is in discussion with the trial collaborators with regards to the likely impact this freeze-thaw-refreeze cycle will have on the samples and biomarker integrity. So far, the discussions have been reassuring from the point of view that the majority of the micronutrient biomarkers are likely to have been degraded in the samples. 

We also note that this non-compliance report is being submitted beyond the recommended five-day window. This is because the full report from the laboratory with sample details was delayed in reaching the PI.
reason_for_deviation: Poor laboratory practice by a member of another project team.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi:
Sample were immediately returned to -80 freezer after notifying the lab manager about the incident. 

Further, to prevent this from reoccurring, the following actions have been recommended by the INDiGO project team to the Keneba laboratory manager:

1. A study-specific freezer is allocated, so non-INDiGO staff are unable to access INDiGO samples.

2. Study freezers are only used for samples and not for the storage of dry ice, ice packs etc.

description_of_deviation:
Participant pair IN-C-018Y and IN-M018C completed assessments for the 6 month 
clinic visit (listed below) outside the infant age range of 6 month (+/-14 days) stated 
within the trial protocol. These assessments were completed on 25 Apr 2024 when the 
infant was 6 months 19 days old. 
This is categorised as a major noncompliance due to impact on the quality of data. 

Assessments Affected 
IN-M-018C: 6mo Clinical Review, 6mo anthropometrics and vital signs, 6mo urine 
sample collection and processing, 6mo blood sample collection and processing, 6mo 
breast milk sample collection and processing.
reason_for_deviation:
The participant pair are residing away from West Kiang for an extended period of time. 
They were notified of their visit on schedule but were not able to attend until 3 weeks 
later.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi: Maintain closer contact with participants in the time leading up to the assessment

description_of_deviation: Urinalysis was not conducted for this participant. . This is in contravention to sections 5.1.2 and 5.1.3 of the INDiGO study protocol (v7.0) where it is stipulated for urinalysis to be conducted for women during the pregnancy phase as a component of the standard antenatal care for these women. These urinalyses are only for clinical care and not related to any of the study's outcomes. Although this test was no performed, the affected women's safety seems uncompromised as all their reviews were all normal (had normal blood pressures, physical assessments, USS and no complaints of ill health during review)
reason_for_deviation: The clinical laboratory which supports the project with this supply ran out of reagent strips for urinalysis on the said dates.
steps_taken_to_correct_thi: The laboratory manager was notified about the incident and reagents were restocked. Henceforth, the clinical laboratory team will ensure that a proper inventory of the urinalysis reagent strips is maintained and is shared with the project team fortnightly. Replenishment of stocks will be initiated once the stock levels is only enough to support this service for 3 months.
